---
description: "Use 28-day periods instead of 30-day — ensures exactly 4 full weeks with equal day distribution"
alwaysApply: true
---

When showing a "monthly" or "~30 day" time period, always use **28 days** instead of 30.

Why: 28 days = exactly 4 complete weeks. Every day of the week appears exactly 4 times. This avoids bias from having different numbers of weekdays vs weekends in the window, which skews traffic and conversion metrics.

- UI labels: "28 days" (not "30 days" or "1 month")
- Filter keys: `28d` (not `30d`)
- Calculations: `Date.now() - 28 * 86400000`
- SQL: `interval '28 days'`
